House Speaker John Boehner has said today that he ‘can’t imagine’ his conservative views on gay marriage will ever shift, even if he had a son who was gay.

The Ohio Republican told ABC News’ Martha Raddatz for ‘This Week’ that he could not possibly see a situation where his views would change.

Rep. Boehner’s firm stance goes directly against the remarkable about-face of fellow Ohio Republican Sen. Rob Portman, who publically said he supports gay marriage after his own son came out.

