When Ms Raddatz asked if he trusted the president, Rep. Boehner said: ‘Absolutely.’

‘The president and I, as I have made clear, have a very good relationship,’ he said. ‘We’re open with each other.‘We’re honest with each other. But we’re trying to bridge some big differences.’

During the interview, Rep. Boehner touched upon several other hot-button issues, including gun control, the recent CPAC conference, and the election of Argentinian Pope Francis, the first South American pope in history.

